  scenario="It is 10:40am on a Friday. You are fitting carpet on a staircase in a four-bedroom house in Reading — the gripper rods are in, the underlay is stapled, and you are stretching the carpet into the first landing turn. Your phone rings in the hallway. A homeowner in Wokingham wants to replace the vinyl in their kitchen and utility room with LVT — they have been quoted by one company already and want a second opinion. Without missed call text-back, they hear your voicemail, do not leave a message, and book with the first company. With missed call text-back, they receive a text at 10:41am: 'Hi, this is [Your Business]. Sorry I missed your call — I am fitting a carpet right now. If you let me know what you need, I will ring you back today.' They reply: 'Hi, looking for LVT in kitchen and utility. About 18 sqm. Had one quote already.' At 12:15pm, you call them with full context and undercut the competition."
